# Plans documentation

Design docs live in [`plans/`](plans/README.md). Update them in the **same change** when you modify related behaviour — do not leave docs stale.

## When to update

| Change | Update |
|--------|--------|
| Terrain Step 1 work (overlay, bake, debug, visual road clip) | `plans/terrain-step1-implementation.md`, status in `plans/terrain-roadmap.md` |
| Terrain bake, atlas, queries, config | `plans/terrain-*.md`, status in `plans/terrain-roadmap.md` |
| Building placement, zones, gap-fill, alleys | `plans/terrain-placement.md` (if terrain-related); roadmap status table |
| New building types or `buildings.yml` terrain fields | `plans/terrain-data-model.md`, `plans/terrain-roadmap.md` |
| Town build pipeline, `Town.h` model | `plans/terrain-data-model.md` if terrain fields added; [`AGENTS.md`](AGENTS.md) for core model |
| Completed roadmap task | Mark task **Done** in `plans/terrain-roadmap.md` and summary in `plans/README.md` |

## How to update

1. Read the relevant `plans/*.md` before large changes to stay aligned with intent.
2. After implementing, edit the matching doc(s): behaviour, file paths, config keys, status tables.
3. If design intent changed, update overview (`terrain-system.md`) — not only the roadmap checkbox.
4. Keep [`AGENTS.md`](AGENTS.md) accurate for **current facts** (coordinates, data model, config). Keep `plans/` for **design and roadmap**.

## Doc map

- `plans/README.md` — index and high-level status
- `plans/terrain-system.md` — goals and architecture
- `plans/terrain-data-model.md` — structs, queries, YAML extensions
- `plans/terrain-bake-pipeline.md` — image → geometry steps
- `plans/terrain-placement.md` — integration with placement and roads
- `plans/terrain-roadmap.md` — phases and task status
- `plans/terrain-step1-implementation.md` — Step 1 task breakdown and acceptance criteria

If a change does not fit existing files, add a focused `plans/<topic>.md` and link it from `plans/README.md`.
